    "Dependency management includes package managers like npm (Node.js), pip (Python), Maven (Java), and NuGet (.NET), which automate the installation, configuration, and versioning of dependencies.",
    "In addition, there exist commercial tools that provide visibility into dependencies and help identify and mitigate security vulnerabilities.",
    "For instance, Sonatype Nexus[204] is a repository manager used for managing software components."
